cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper focuses on feature selection for text categorization, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new approach based on statistical analysis, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and data science (DS), suggesting cs.LG and cs.DS as likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with feature selection, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
